# Notes API
Notes API is a *short texts saving* service similar to its physical paper presence on your table.

# Group Notes
Notes related resources of the **Notes API**

## Notes Collection [/notes]
### List all Notes [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json; charset=utf-8)

        [{
        "id": 2,
        "title": "Second Note",
        "note": "This is my second note",
        "edited_by": "OUTOUN"
        },
        {
        "id": 3,
        "title": "Third Note",
        "note": "This is my third note",
        "edited_by": "Uness"
        },
        {
        "id": 4,
        "title": "Fourth Note",
        "note": "This is the note content 4",
        "edited_by": "UIPS"
        }]

### Create a Note [POST]
+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "id": 6,
            "title": "Sixth Note",
            "note": "This is the note content 6",
            "edited_by": "Uness"
        }

+ Response 200 (application/json; charset=utf-8)

        {
            "success" : true,
            "message" : "Your note was inserted successfully"
        }

## Notes Collection [/edit_note]
### Update a Note [POST]

+ Request (application/json)

        {
          "id": 5,
          "title": "Fifth Note",
          "note": "This is the note content 5",
          "edited_by": "Uness"
         }

+ Response 200 (application/json; charset=utf-8)

        {
            "success" : true,
            "message" : "Your note was updated successfully"
        }

## Note [GET /note/{id}]
A single Note object with all its details

+ Parameters
    + id: `2` (number, required) - Numeric `id` to get note with. Has example value.

+ Response 200 (application/json; charset=utf-8)

        {
           "id": 2, 
           "title": "Second Note", 
           "note": "This is my second note", 
           "edited_by": "OUTOUN"
        }


## Note deletion [/note/{id}]
### Remove a Note [DELETE]

+ Parameters
    + id: `5` (number, required) - Numeric `id` to delete note with.

+ Response 200 (application/json; charset=utf-8)

        {
           "success" : true,
           "message" : "Your note was deleted successfully"
        }